block content 
    h1.bd-title#content Button group
    p.bd-lead Group a series of buttons together on a single line with the button group, and super-power them with JavaScript.

    h2#basic-example Basic example
    p
        | Wrap a series of buttons with 
        code.highlighter-rouge .btn
        |  in 
        code.highlighter-rouge .btn-group
        | . Add on optional JavaScript radio and checkbox style behavior with 
        a(href='/docs/4.1/components/buttons/#button-plugin') our buttons plugin
        | .
    .bd-example
        .btn-group(role='group', aria-label='Basic example')
            +btn-secondary('Left') 
            +btn-secondary('Middle') 
            +btn-secondary('Right')

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                .btn-group(role='group', aria-label='Basic example')
                    +btn-secondary('Left') 
                    +btn-secondary('Middle') 
                    +btn-secondary('Right')
    
    .bd-callout.bd-callout-warning
        h5#ensure-correct-role-and-provide-a-label
            | Ensure correct 
            code.highlighter-rouge role
            |  and provide a label
        p
            | In order for assistive technologies (such as screen readers) to convey that a series of buttons is grouped, an appropriate 
            code.highlighter-rouge role
            |  attribute needs to be provided. For button groups, this would be 
            code.highlighter-rouge role="group"
            | , while toolbars should have a 
            code.highlighter-rouge role="toolbar"
            | .
        p
            | In addition, groups and toolbars should be given an explicit label, as most assistive technologies will otherwise not announce them, despite the presence of the correct role attribute. In the examples provided here, we use 
            code.highlighter-rouge aria-label
            | , but alternatives such as 
            code.highlighter-rouge aria-labelledby
            |  can also be used.
    h2#button-toolbar Button toolbar
    p
        | Combine sets of button groups into button toolbars for more complex components. Use utility classes as needed to space out groups, buttons, and more.
    .bd-example
        .btn-toolbar(role='toolbar', aria-label='Toolbar with button groups')
            .btn-group.mr-2(role='group', aria-label='First group')
                +btn-secondary('1')
                +btn-secondary('2')
                +btn-secondary('3')
                +btn-secondary('4')
            .btn-group.mr-2(role='group', aria-label='Second group')
                +btn-secondary('5')
                +btn-secondary('6')
                +btn-secondary('7')
            .btn-group(role='group', aria-label='Third group')
                +btn-secondary('8')

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                .btn-toolbar(role='toolbar', aria-label='Toolbar with button groups')
                    .btn-group.mr-2(role='group', aria-label='First group')
                        +btn-secondary('1')
                        +btn-secondary('2')
                        +btn-secondary('3')
                        +btn-secondary('4')
                    .btn-group.mr-2(role='group', aria-label='Second group')
                        +btn-secondary('5')
                        +btn-secondary('6')
                        +btn-secondary('7')
                    .btn-group(role='group', aria-label='Third group')
                        +btn-secondary('8')

    p
        | Feel free to mix input groups with button groups in your toolbars. Similar to the example above, youâ€™ll likely need some utilities though to space things properly.
    .bd-example
        .btn-toolbar.mb-3(role='toolbar', aria-label='Toolbar with button groups')
            .btn-group.mr-2(role='group', aria-label='First group')
                +btn-secondary('1')
                +btn-secondary('2')
                +btn-secondary('3')
                +btn-secondary('4')
            +input-group('@')
                +input('text','textInput','Input group example')
        .btn-toolbar.justify-content-between(role='toolbar', aria-label='Toolbar with button groups')
            .btn-group(role='group', aria-label='First group')
                +btn-secondary('1')
                +btn-secondary('2')
                +btn-secondary('3')
                +btn-secondary('4')
            +input-group('@')
                +input('text','textInput','Input group example')

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                .btn-toolbar.mb-3(role='toolbar', aria-label='Toolbar with button groups')
                    .btn-group.mr-2(role='group', aria-label='First group')
                        +btn-secondary('1')
                        +btn-secondary('2')
                        +btn-secondary('3')
                        +btn-secondary('4')
                    +input-group('@')
                        +input('text','textInput','Input group example')
                .btn-toolbar.justify-content-between(role='toolbar', aria-label='Toolbar with button groups')
                    .btn-group(role='group', aria-label='First group')
                        +btn-secondary('1')
                        +btn-secondary('2')
                        +btn-secondary('3')
                        +btn-secondary('4')
                    +input-group('@')
                        +input('text','textInput','Input group example')

    h2#sizing Sizing
    p
        | Instead of applying button sizing classes to every button in a group, just add 
        code.highlighter-rouge .btn-group-*
        |  to each 
        code.highlighter-rouge .btn-group
        | , including each one when nesting multiple groups.
    .bd-example
        .btn-group.btn-group-lg(role='group', aria-label='Large button group')
            +btn-secondary('Left') 
            +btn-secondary('Middle') 
            +btn-secondary('Right')
        br
        .btn-group(role='group', aria-label='Default button group')
            +btn-secondary('Left') 
            +btn-secondary('Middle') 
            +btn-secondary('Right')
        br
        .btn-group.btn-group-sm(role='group', aria-label='Small button group')
            +btn-secondary('Left') 
            +btn-secondary('Middle') 
            +btn-secondary('Right')

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                .btn-group.btn-group-lg(role='group', aria-label='Large button group')
                    +btn-secondary('Left') 
                    +btn-secondary('Middle') 
                    +btn-secondary('Right')
                
                .btn-group(role='group', aria-label='Default button group')
                    +btn-secondary('Left') 
                    +btn-secondary('Middle') 
                    +btn-secondary('Right')
                
                .btn-group.btn-group-sm(role='group', aria-label='Small button group')
                    +btn-secondary('Left') 
                    +btn-secondary('Middle') 
                    +btn-secondary('Right')

    h2#nesting Nesting
    p
        | Place a 
        code.highlighter-rouge .btn-group
        |  within another 
        code.highlighter-rouge .btn-group
        |  when you want dropdown menus mixed with a series of buttons.
    .bd-example
        .btn-group(role='group', aria-label='Button group with nested dropdown')
            +btn-secondary('1') 
            +btn-secondary('2') 
            +dropdown-secondary('Dropdown',[
                {text:'Dropdown link',data:'#'},
                {text:'Dropdown link',data:'#'}
            ])
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                .btn-group(role='group', aria-label='Button group with nested dropdown')
                    +btn-secondary('1') 
                    +btn-secondary('2') 
                    +dropdown-secondary('Dropdown',[
                        {text:'Dropdown link',data:'#'},
                        {text:'Dropdown link',data:'#'}
                    ])
